    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<pre><code>String one, two, three;\none = two = three = \"\";\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>This should work with immutable objects. It doesn't make any sense for mutable objects for example:</p>\n\n<pre><code>Person firstPerson, secondPerson, thirdPerson;\nfirstPerson = secondPerson = thirdPerson = new Person();\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>All the variables would be pointing to the same instance. Probably what you would need in that case is:</p>\n\n<pre><code>Person firstPerson = new Person();\nPerson secondPerson = new Person();\nPerson thirdPerson = new Person();\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Or better yet use an array or a <a href=\"https://docs.oracle.com/javase/10/docs/api/java/util/Collection.html\" rel=\"noreferrer\"><code>Collection</code></a>.</p>\n"
  }, {
