      "body" : "@GeorgPlaz Well, I&#39;m struggling to think of instances where one would <i>want</i> to have three pointers to the same object initialized all at once in this manner - so, in most cases (unless one knows exactly what one is doing), having three pointers to the same object may not be the desired outcome (and would be perceived as &#39;misbehaviour&#39;)."
