    "creation_date" : 1345572222,
    "answer_id" : 12060516,
    "question_id" : 6202818,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Works for primitives and immutable classes like <code>String</code>, Wrapper classes Character, Byte.</p>\n<pre><code>int i=0,j=2   \nString s1,s2  \ns1 = s2 = &quot;java rocks&quot;\n</code></pre>\n<p>For mutable classes</p>\n<pre><code>Reference r1 = Reference r2 = Reference r3 = new Object();\n</code></pre>\n<p>Three references + one object are created. All references point to the same object and your program will misbehave.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "comments" : [ {
      "owner" : {
        "account_id" : 6179811,
        "reputation" : 376,
        "user_id" : 7206367,
        "user_type" : "registered",
