      "creation_date" : 1692902374,
      "post_id" : 31910261,
      "comment_id" : 135691064,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
      "body" : "This is also works with final vars. Ex: public static final String ONE, TWO = ONE = &quot;Blah&quot;; Not only are all vars defined &amp; initialized to the same value, but the split definition &amp; assignment of var ONE doesn&#39;t violate the final limitation; it&#39;s considered a single expression."
    } ],
