    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 4.0",
    "body" : "<p>Edit: As Zeeen pointed out this will not work in Java. The question I'd intended to answer was in Groovy as well, this was submitted in error.</p>\n<hr />\n<p>Way too late to this but the simplest way I've found is:</p>\n<pre><code>String foo = bar = baz = &quot;hello&quot;\nprintln(foo)\nprintln(bar)\nprintln(baz)\n</code></pre>\n<p>Output:</p>\n<pre><code>hello\nhello\nhello\n</code></pre>\n"
