  "title" : "Initializing multiple variables to the same value in Java",
  "body" : "<p>I'm looking for a clean and efficient method of declaring multiple variables of the same type and of the same value. Right now I have:</p>\n\n<pre><code>String one = \"\", two = \"\", three = \"\" etc...\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>But I'm looking for something like:</p>\n\n<pre><code>String one,two,three = \"\"\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>Is this something that is possible to do in java? Keeping efficiency in mind.</p>\n"
